      <h2>The Service</h2>
      <p>LockPact provides mutual screen time accountability between two people. Here's what LockPact does:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Allows you to select apps on your device that you want to block during certain times</li>
        <li>Uses Apple's Screen Time API to enforce these blocks</li>
        <li>Shares lock status and bypass events with your paired partner via push notifications</li>
        <li>Enables you to request unlocks from your partner, who can approve or deny the request</li>
        <li>Detects when you bypass Screen Time restrictions on your own device and notifies your partner</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Important: The device owner can always bypass Screen Time restrictions by going to Settings &gt; Screen Time &gt; App Limits, entering Face ID or passcode, and disabling the restriction. LockPact cannot prevent this—it can only detect and report it to your partner.</strong> The value of LockPact is social accountability, not technical enforcement.</p>

