      <h2>Partnership and Pairing</h2>
      <p>LockPact partnerships are based on voluntary, active consent from both users. To pair:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>One user generates a unique 6-digit invite code in the app</li>
        <li>The other user enters this code within the designated time window</li>
        <li>Both users are shown confirmation that the partnership is active</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Both partners must actively consent to pairing. Do not use invite codes to pair with someone without their knowledge or consent.</strong></p>
      <p>Either partner can dissolve the partnership at any time via Settings &gt; Partnership &gt; End Partnership. When a partnership is dissolved, lock status synchronization stops immediately, but historical data remains in your account for 30 days before deletion.</p>
      <p>When you are paired with a partner, the following information is shared:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your lock status (locked or unlocked)</li>
        <li>Bypass events (when you bypass a lock)</li>
        <li>Unlock request text (the reason you provided when requesting an unlock)</li>
        <li>Unlock approvals and denials</li>
        <li>Streak information (consecutive days of locked status)</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Do not share private information in unlock request reasons if you do not want your partner to see it.</strong></p>

      <h2>Unlock Requests</h2>
      <p>You may request an unlock from your partner at any time. When you submit an unlock request:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You can optionally provide a reason (text) for the unlock request</li>
        <li>Your partner receives a push notification and can approve or deny your request within the app</li>
        <li>If approved, the lock is released for a time period you choose during the request</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Before an unlock request is sent, you are presented with a confirmation dialog offering two equal options:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Watch &amp; Request:</strong> View a 30–60 second rewarded video advertisement, after which your unlock request is sent to your partner.</li>
        <li><strong>Willpower Waiver:</strong> Skip the advertisement by purchasing the Willpower Waiver, a one-time non-consumable in-app purchase. After purchase, subsequent unlock requests can be sent without watching an ad. When you use the Waiver, your partner sees a "Used Willpower Waiver" label on the unlock request, and your solo lock history will note when a Waiver was used.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The same two-option dialog is presented if you end a solo lock early.</p>

      <h2>In-App Purchases and Tips</h2>
      <p>LockPact offers the following paid transactions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Willpower Waiver</strong> (iOS in-app purchase, one-time non-consumable) — described above.</li>
        <li><strong>Tip Jar</strong> (iOS in-app purchases, consumable; available in three tiers) — voluntary support that unlocks no features. Tips are non-refundable purchases that contribute to operating costs and continued development.</li>
        <li><strong>Tip Jar (web)</strong> — voluntary tips may also be made through Stripe Checkout at <a href="/support-lockpact">lockpact.app/support-lockpact</a>. Web payments are processed by Stripe, Inc.; iOS purchases are processed by Apple Inc. through the App Store.</li>
      </ul>

